00:18:43.150 --> 00:18:47.160
and how we, as a species,
co-evolved with dogs

00:18:47.160 --> 00:18:51.430
in forming those relationships
to the point that today,

00:18:51.430 --> 00:18:55.060
you could say that they
really are part of our society

00:18:55.060 --> 00:18:57.360
rather than just us
using them as tools.

00:18:57.360 --> 00:18:59.830
I was curious as to your
opinion on that relationship.

00:18:59.830 --> 00:19:01.330
MARK MOFFETT: Yeah,
I think they can

00:19:01.330 --> 00:19:02.800
be viewed as part of society.

00:19:02.800 --> 00:19:04.008
I had a paragraph about this.

00:19:04.008 --> 00:19:05.508
It's one of these
little things that

00:19:05.508 --> 00:19:06.880
